<F P=100> SOUTH ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Afghanistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Mazar-e Sharif Airport Forced To Shut Down </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Mazar-e Sharif Airport Forced To Shut Down </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1805163994 Kabul Radio Afghanistan Network in Pashto 1530 
GMT 18 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1805163994 </F>
<F P=104>  Kabul Radio Afghanistan Network </F>
<F P=105>  Pashto </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Mazar-e Sharif Airport cannot be used for flights. 
Bakhtar has received reports from Mazar-e Sharif that during 
recent days the airport, from where aircraft of the infamous 
militias [word indistinct], has been under heavy weapon fire by 
Mojahedin and forces of the Islamic Army. This airport has been 
put out of operation completely. 

</TEXT>

